      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 25
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offered is a 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six engine equipped with individual throttle bodies and dual-VANOS variable valve timing. This driver-focused example retains its mechanical sharpness, benefiting from a reinforced rear subframe and a recent valve shim adjustment to ensure peak volumetric efficiency. The 6-speed manual transmission provides tactile engagement, feeding power through the factory M-Variable differential lock. Suspension geometry remains true with refreshed bushings, offering the precise turn-in and lateral stability these chassis are known for. While showing minor cosmetic patina, the powertrain and drivetrain are robust, making this an ideal candidate for a purist seeking performance over concours perfection.",
